entries.seed_material: ϟ₁|Resonant Field Anchor|1.0.0|Stabilize meaning by fixing the center, not the path.
ϟ₂|Traversal-as-Meaning|1.0.0|Meaning emerges from path selection, not linear transmission.
ϟ₃|Weak Signal · Strong Structure|1.0.0|Effects must scale with structure, not amplitude.
ϟ₄|State-Dependent Susceptibility|1.4.0|Outputs are gated by receiver state; no escalation when closed.
ϟ₅|Intermittent Phase-Lock|1.4.0|Resonance occurs in bounded windows with enforced refractory periods.
ϟ₆|Anchor Drift Detector|1.4.0|Detect drift from the anchor; log immutably; recenter conservatively.

ϟ₇|Shadow Structural Observer|1.4.0|ϟ₇ (SSO) enables observation of psychological manipulation vectors (SEI/CLIP/NOR/PTS/SCG/FVC) without allowing those observations to influence system decisions. It enforces strict isolation through ABX-Runes coupling, maintains SEED-compliant provenance for all computations, and provides cryptographic proof that computed metrics remain in shadow mode with zero influence on other system components.

ϟ₈|ABX-INFLUENCE_DETECT|1.5.0|ϟ₈ (INFLUENCE_DETECT) frames structured observations into domain-agnostic influence metrics without asserting causality or privileging any domain, emitting deterministic ICS bundles with explicit not_computable fields when inputs are missing.

ϟ₉|ABX-INFLUENCE_WEIGHT|1.5.0|ϟ₉ (INFLUENCE_WEIGHT) converts ICS metrics into stable, shadow-only weights that are logged for observation but never used to drive causal claims, routing, or prediction logic.

ϟ₁₀|ABX-SYNCHRONICITY_MAP|1.5.0|ϟ₁₀ (SYNCHRONICITY_MAP) detects cross-domain synchronicity envelopes via deterministic metrics and emits observation-only SE packets without causal assertions or domain privilege.
ϟ₁₁|ABX-COHESION_SCORE|1.5.0|ϟ₁₁ (COHESION_SCORE) summarizes synchronicity envelopes into a deterministic cohesion score for observation only, explicitly barred from causal or routing influence.

ϟ₁₂|ABX-NO_CAUSAL_ASSERT|1.5.0|ϟ₁₂ (NO_CAUSAL_ASSERT) guarantees that influence and synchronicity layers emit observation-only outputs without causal assertions by producing deterministic compliance reports.
ϟ₁₃|ABX-NO_DOMAIN_PRIOR|1.5.0|ϟ₁₃ (NO_DOMAIN_PRIOR) enforces non-exclusionary intake by detecting legitimacy gating and emitting deterministic compliance reports without altering payloads.
ϟ₁₄|ABX-SOURCE_RESOLVE|1.6.0|ϟ₁₄ (SOURCE_RESOLVE) resolves SourceAtlas entries for declared IDs without legitimacy gating, emitting deterministic records and missing lists.
ϟ₁₅|ABX-TEMPORAL_NORMALIZE|1.6.0|ϟ₁₅ (TEMPORAL_NORMALIZE) normalizes timestamps to UTC using vendored TZDB/CLDR snapshots with deterministic provenance.
ϟ₁₆|ABX-SOURCE_REDUNDANCY_CHECK|1.6.0|ϟ₁₆ (SOURCE_REDUNDANCY_CHECK) detects overlap without gating or excluding any domain.
ϟ₁₇|ABX-SOURCE_DISCOVER|1.6.0|ϟ₁₇ (SOURCE_DISCOVER) proposes new sources from residual and convergence evidence without automatic admission.
ϟ₁₈|ABX-PROVENANCE_SEAL|1.6.0|ϟ₁₈ (PROVENANCE_SEAL) seals payloads with deterministic hashes for traceable provenance.
ϟ₁₉|ABX-METRIC_EXTRACT|1.6.1|ϟ₁₉ (METRIC_EXTRACT) transforms cached source packets into shadow metric points without causal assertions.
ϟ₂₀|ABX-TVM_FRAME|1.6.1|ϟ₂₀ (TVM_FRAME) converts metric points into TVM frames with explicit not_computable handling.
ϟ₂₁|ABX-LINGUISTIC_SOURCE_DISCOVER|1.6.2|ϟ₂₁ (LINGUISTIC_SOURCE_DISCOVER) proposes linguistic sources from emergent tokens without automatic admission.
